\title{Transclusion Trees}
\taxon{section}
\date{2026-04-04}
\tag{transclusion}
\meta{description}{The rooted trees traced from skills with no parents and 4+ children}

\import{macros}

\p{12 root trees span the connected component. Each root has no parent references and 4 or more children.}

\subtree{
\title{load-skills (12 children)}
\p{Bootstrap loader. First skill loaded in every session. Fans out to:}
\ul{
\li{[[aptos-agent]] → [[aptos-trading]]}
\li{[[bisimulation-game]] → [[coequalizers]] → [[ordered-locale]] → [[unworld]]}
\li{[[ruler-maximal]] → [[dialectica]], [[kan-extensions]], [[open-games]], [[sheaf-cohomology]], [[yoneda-directed]]}
\li{[[parallel-fanout]] → [[epistemic-arbitrage]], [[spi-parallel-verify]]}
\li{[[say-narration]], [[skill-creator]], [[skill-validation-gf3]]}
}
\p{Depth to [[unworld]]: 4. Depth to [[gay-mcp]] via ordered-locale: 5.}
}

\subtree{
\title{homoiconic-rewriting (11 children)}
\p{Lambda calculus, interaction nets, ACSets, CUDA parallelism unified under graph rewriting.}
\ul{
\li{[[algebraic-rewriting]] → [[topos-adhesive-rewriting]] → [[acsets-relational-thinking]] → [[unworld]]}
\li{[[interaction-nets]] → [[lambda-calculus]], [[linear-logic]], [[propagators]]}
\li{[[gay-mcp]], [[lispsyntax-acset]], [[slime-lisp]] → [[cider-clojure]]}
}
\p{This tree bridges categorical algebra to Lisp tooling. The only path from [[lambda-calculus]] to [[gay-mcp]].}
}

\subtree{
\title{latent-latency (8 children)}
\p{Thermodynamic learning theory. Connects Fokker-Planck dynamics to entropy sequencing.}
\ul{
\li{[[fokker-planck-analyzer]] → [[entropy-sequencer]] → [[agent-o-rama]], [[cybernetic-immune]], [[three-match]]}
\li{[[langevin-dynamics]] → SDE-based learning}
\li{[[mcp-tripartite]] → 19 children (largest single subtree)}
\li{[[ramanujan-expander]] → [[ihara-zeta]] → [[moebius-inversion]]}
}
\p{Deepest tree. Reaches [[autopoiesis]] at depth 6 via cybernetic-immune.}
}

\subtree{
\title{infinity-operads (7 children)}
\p{Higher categorical structure for multi-input composition.}
\ul{
\li{[[asi-polynomial-operads]] → [[discohy-streams]] → [[gay-mcp]], [[three-match]], [[world-hopping]]}
\li{[[catsharp]] → [[structured-decomp]] → [[specter-acset]]}
\li{[[kinetic-block]] (25 children — largest single skill by out-degree)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{cats-for-ai (7 children)}
\p{Category theory applied to artificial intelligence.}
\ul{
\li{[[cybernetic-open-game]] (17 children) → [[cognitive-superposition]] (13 children) → [[godel-machine]], [[gflownet]], [[kolmogorov-compression]]}
\li{[[topos-catcolab]] → [[acsets-relational-thinking]] → [[unworld]]}
\li{[[derangement-crdt]] → [[crdt-vterm]] → [[spi-parallel-verify]]}
}
\p{The widest tree. Reaches 50+ unique skills within depth 4.}
}

